quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  43,1,"Ha Mīm."
  43,2,"By the Evident Scripture,"
  43,3,"indeed, We made it an Arabic Recital{1}, that you<sup>pl </sup>may reason.",1:[The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
  43,4,"And indeed, it is with Us in the Source of Scriptures, all-high, all-wise."
  43,5,"So shall We ignore reminding you<sup>pl </sup>, for having been{1}an extremist people?",1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i, Abu Ja’far and Khalaf read it as: “…you<sup>pl</sup>, if you have been an extremist people?”]
  43,6,"And how many a prophet did We send to the ancients!"
  43,7,"Yet not a prophet came to them but that they used to ridicule him."
  43,8,"Thus We annihilated people more powerful than them, and so the example of the ancients has passed away."
  43,9,"And were you<sup>sg </sup>to ask them, “Who created the heavens and the earth?” They would say, “The Almighty, the All-Knowing created them.”"
  43,10,"He Who made the earth a cradle{1} for you<sup>pl </sup>and traced in it ways for you, that you may be guided.",1:[Qira’at: All except for Asem, Hamza, Al Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…a resting place for you…”]
